<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Townes, 1981" authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1981" box="[323,773,188,213]" class="Hexapoda" family="Proctotrupidae" genus="Sminthoserphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="defrictus">
<emphasis box="[323,607,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Sminthоserphus defrictus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Townes" box="[616,773,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" refString="Townes, H. &amp; Townes, M. (1981) A revision of the Serphidae (Hymenoptera). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 32, 1 - 541." type="journal article" year="1981">Townes, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was placed in the South American 
<taxonomicName box="[1179,1358,188,213]" class="Hexapoda" family="Proctotrupidae" genus="Sminthoserphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1179,1358,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Sminthоserphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of its superficial similarity to other members of the genus. Scrutiny of 
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1135,223,248]" class="Hexapoda" family="Proctotrupidae" genus="Sminthoserphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="defrictus">
<emphasis box="[1009,1135,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">S. defrictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
characters has proved that the species does not belong to 
<taxonomicName box="[494,673,260,285]" class="Hexapoda" family="Proctotrupidae" genus="Sminthoserphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[494,673,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Sminthоserphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and should be included in the new genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1142,1307,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Proctotrupidae" genus="Trachyserphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1142,1307,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Trachyserphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The edges of the syntergite in 
<taxonomicName box="[385,515,295,320]" class="Hexapoda" family="Proctotrupidae" genus="Sminthoserphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="defrictus">
<emphasis box="[385,515,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">S. defrictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are broadly overlapping ventrally along its posterior third, whereas species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,330,332,357]" class="Hexapoda" family="Proctotrupidae" genus="Sminthoserphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,330,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Sminthоserphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by non-overlapping syntergite edges that leave a wide portion of the synsternite visible.
</paragraph>
